edu.uta.cse.fireeye.common
Class Parameter

java.lang.Object
  edu.uta.cse.fireeye.common.Parameter

public class Parameter
extends java.lang.Object

This class represents a Parameter in a system configuration. Each parameter has a list of values, which can be one of the three types, boolean, integer, and enum. Type enum is essentially a string type.

Each parameter has two IDs. Both IDs are automatically assigned by the SUT object into which this parameter is added.

  • ID: This ID indicates the order of parameters as specified by the user.
  • ActiveID: This indicates the order of parameters covered by the IPOG strategy, which reorders parameters as needed to achieve optimal results.
